snippet: Natalie Geisenberger of Germany clinched the overall luge World Cup title by beating the American Julia Clukey by 0.295 of a second in Lake Placid.
abstract: Natalie Geisenberger of Germany defeats American Julia Clukey to clinch overall luge World Cup title in Lake Placid, NY.
lead_paragraph: Natalie Geisenberger of Germany clinched the overall luge World Cup title by beating the American Julia Clukey by 0.295 of a second in Lake Placid.

headline.seo: Natalie Geisenberger of Germany Seals Luge World Cup Title
headline.main: German Seals Luge World Cup Title
